    cellular: "Radiation protection follows the ALARA principle. Ionizing radiation causes deterministic effects (threshold-based like skin erythema and cataracts) and stochastic effects (probabilistic including cancer). The three cardinal principles are time, distance, and shielding. The inverse square law states doubling distance reduces exposure to one-quarter. Lead aprons of 0.5 mm Pb attenuate 95-99% of scatter at diagnostic energies. Dose limits: occupational whole-body 50 mSv/year, lens 150 mSv/year, extremity 500 mSv/year, embryo/fetus 5 mSv total gestation, public 1 mSv/year. Personnel monitoring uses OSL or TLD dosimeters worn at collar level.",
