    cellular: "CT chest protocols include non-contrast for lung screening and pulmonary assessment, contrast-enhanced for mediastinal evaluation, and CT pulmonary angiography (CTPA) for PE using bolus tracking. CT abdomen/pelvis is performed with oral and/or IV contrast in arterial, portal venous, or delayed phases depending on indication. Typical protocols: non-contrast for renal calculi, arterial phase for liver lesion characterization and vascular assessment, portal venous phase for general abdominal survey, delayed phase for urinary tract evaluation. Dose optimization includes BMI-based protocols and organ-specific dose modulation.",
