    title: "Lateral Decubitus and Cross-Table Techniques",
    cellular: "Lateral decubitus positioning places the patient on their side for specific diagnostic purposes. Left lateral decubitus (left side down) with horizontal beam detects free air between the liver and right abdominal wall (pneumoperitoneum). Right lateral decubitus (right side down) shows free fluid layering along the right chest wall (pleural effusion). Cross-table lateral technique uses a horizontal beam with the patient supine, used in trauma for lateral cervical spine and lateral hip when the patient cannot be moved. These techniques require horizontal beam alignment and adequate exposure time.",
