    cellular: "Interventional radiology uses image guidance to perform minimally invasive diagnostic and therapeutic procedures. The Seldinger technique is the foundation: needle access, guidewire insertion, catheter placement over the wire. Common procedures include angioplasty (balloon dilation of stenosed vessels), stent placement, embolization (blocking blood supply to tumors or bleeding), abscess drainage, biopsy, and TIPS (transjugular intrahepatic portosystemic shunt). The technologist prepares sterile equipment, assists with catheter/guidewire management, operates imaging equipment, and monitors patient vitals. Post-procedure monitoring includes puncture site assessment for hematoma and distal pulse checks.",
