    title: "Tomosynthesis Imaging",
    cellular: "Digital tomosynthesis acquires multiple low-dose projections at different angles and reconstructs thin slices through the volume of interest. In breast tomosynthesis (DBT), the tube arcs through 15-50 degrees, acquiring 9-25 projections. Reconstruction produces 1mm slices through the breast, reducing tissue overlap that limits conventional mammography. DBT increases cancer detection rates by 20-40% in dense breasts and reduces false-positive recall rates. Chest tomosynthesis can improve detection of pulmonary nodules and mediastinal lesions. Total radiation dose for DBT is comparable to or slightly higher than standard 2D mammography.",
